NAME
    gcloud alpha spanner databases describe - describe a Cloud Spanner database

SYNOPSIS
    gcloud alpha spanner databases describe (DATABASE : --instance=INSTANCE)
        [GCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG ...]

DESCRIPTION
    (ALPHA) Describe a Cloud Spanner database.

POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS
     Database resource - The Cloud Spanner database to describe. The arguments
     in this group can be used to specify the attributes of this resource.
     (NOTE) Some attributes are not given arguments in this group but can be
     set in other ways. To set the [project] attribute: provide the flag
     [database] on the command line with a fully specified name; provide the
     flag [--project] on the command line; set the property [core/project].
     This must be specified.

       DATABASE
          The ID of the database or a fully qualified identifier for the
          database. This positional must be specified if any of the other
          arguments in this group are specified.

       --instance=INSTANCE
          The Cloud Spanner instance for the database.

GCLOUD WIDE FLAGS
    These flags are available to all commands: --account, --configuration,
    --flatten, --format, --help, --log-http, --project, --quiet, --trace-token,
    --user-output-enabled, --verbosity. Run $ gcloud help for details.

NOTES
    This command is currently in ALPHA and may change without notice. If this
    command fails with API permission errors despite specifying the right
    project, you will have to apply for early access and have your projects
    registered on the API whitelist to use it. To do so, contact Support at
    https://cloud.google.com/support/. These variants are also available:

        $ gcloud spanner databases describe
        $ gcloud beta spanner databases describe

